    </div>
    <div class="lightbox__inner">
      <div class="lightbox__image">
        <img src={journeyMapImage.src} alt="Journey map" draggable="false" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </dialog>
  <p class="image-row--caption">
    To anchor the redevelopment, I mapped the two-year lifecycle of a Consultant
    business to clarify how live delivery connected to preparation,
    administration and reporting. The map became a reference point across the
    Consultant ecosystem.
  </p>
  <section class="card content-block">
    <h2>Approach</h2>

    <p>
      Working directly with board members and senior stakeholders, I defined the
      live-session experience in detail — down to information hierarchy and
      visibility guidelines.
    </p>

    <p>
      Through co-design workshops and a <a
        href="https://www.uxforthemasses.com/buy-the-feature/"
        target="_blank">“buy-your-data”</a
      >
      prioritisation exercise with senior Consultants and the company owner, we reviewed
      each data point and agreed what genuinely needed to surface during the session.
    </p>
    <p>
      Service safaris with product and engineering built a shared understanding
      of the live environment. A subsequent Six Thinking Hats session tested
      assumptions against operational and technical constraints before moving
      forward.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="full-bleed--text full-bleed--text__standout-quote">
    <blockquote>
      <span class="blockquote--small offset-right">
        &ldquo;&hellip;the information for stage one needs to
      </span><span class="blockquote--large offset-left">
        smack you in the face&rdquo;</span
      >

      <cite> - Director of the Field</cite>
    </blockquote>
  </section>
  <p class="image-row--caption">
    I returned to this comment throughout the process as a way of grounding
    conversations about clarity and prioritisation.
  </p>
  <section class="card content-block">
    <h2>Outcome</h2>
    <p>Through structured critique and iteration, I defined:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>A clearer on-screen information hierarchy</li>
      <li>Simplified visibility rules</li>
      <li>
        A consistent approach to prioritising data during the live session
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Decisions were often revisited and refined, with trade-offs discussed in
      context rather than against fixed rules.
    </p>

    <p>
      The direction was translated into interactive Figma prototypes and
      reviewed with board members and stakeholders. Informal hallway testing
      with Consultants helped refine the approach.
    </p>
    <p>
      After multiple rounds of iteration, <strong>
        the design was ready to move into simulated group testing.
      </strong>
    </p>
  </section>

