  <section class="card content-block" id="scroll-target">
    <h2>A slight pivot</h2>
    <p>
      As the iterative design phase concluded, the company made a methodological
      shift. The Consultant’s role moved from structured one-to-one support to a
      more facilitative, member-led format.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>
        The earlier position — “We’re not changing the group process.” — no
        longer applied.
      </strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      To understand the implications, I observed the roll-out training and
      attended groups to see how the new format was working in practice.
    </p>
    <p>
      It became clear the tool needed to evolve to support a different group
      dynamic. Rather than discarding the existing work, I adapted.
    </p>
    <p>
      I introduced an index layer in front of the existing screens — a
      stripped-back, in-the-moment summary of all members — while preserving
      immediate access to the deeper data set already defined through research
      and prioritisation.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="image-row image-row--full-bleed image-row--3">
