  <p class="image-row--caption">
    I introduced a new index to improve scanability during live sessions, giving
    Consultants an at-a-glance view of all members in the room. <br /><br />The
    structure followed a hub-and-spoke navigation pattern, with the index as the
    hub and individual member screens as spokes. This enabled flexible,
    non-linear movement between members as needed, in support of the group
    conversation.
  </p>
  <section class="card content-block">
    <h2>Advanced prototyping</h2>
    <p>
      Having iterated on the index in Figma, I rebuilt the full prototype in
      Figma Make's AI-assisted code generation to better simulate a live
      application.
    </p>
    <p>
      Using prompt-driven logic and lightweight code, I generated dynamic
      datasets, introduced event-driven interactions and maintained state across
      member views. This enabled behaviour that would have been difficult to
      model using standard Figma prototyping alone.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="image-row image-row--full-bleed image-row--3">
    <!-- <img src="/images/xpress-weigh/figma/figma-make0.png" alt="" /> -->
    <Image
      src={figmaMake1Image}
      alt=""
      widths={[480, 768, 1024, 1440, 1920]}
      sizes="100vw"
    />
    <Image
      src={figmaMake2Image}
